As mothers, part of our job is to remind our daughters to love their hair and treat it well, whichever style they’re rocking. Braids are a tried-and-test style that is school-friendly, saves us hours and looks good! It’s important to remember that an adult’s scalp can handle a lot more pressure than a child’s can, so braids that aren’t done with care can cause damage. Hair expert Carice Anderson told DESTINY in a previous article that braids should never be too tight, too heavy or too thin, especially around the hairline. This rule applies even more strictly to children. 